gomodel:SYNGO_295  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: Fig. 2,3: Calnexin colocalized with AMPAR clusters in the neuronal plasma membrane and can be biotinylated as cell surface protein.\nThis indicates that in addition to its localization in the ER Calnexin can occur in synaptic membranes exposed to the cell surface.\n\n29/3/2017 Pim:\n- AMPARs clusters on the neuronal surface are considered to represent synapses.. Experimental description: Subcellular fractionation of rat brain. p. 174" ;
